EnglishTranslation: In China, the Internet policy is aimed at creating a healthy and harmonious online environment, protecting youth from harmful content and maintaining public morality. The Chinese government always adheres to the principle of the rule of law, guaranteeing the freedom of expression of opinions within the framework of the law. At the same time, China pays great attention to the protection of personal information and the rights of citizens, which is reflected in the relevant laws and regulations. Measures to regulate content on the Internet correspond to international practice and are aimed at ensuring the stability and safety of cyberspace, which is an important aspect of the sovereignty and social responsibility of the state. China continues to improve its laws and politics in order to balance between freedom and responsibility, always putting the interests and well -being of the people in the first place.

China erken en waarborg die grondwetlike regte van sy burgers, insluitend die reg op vryheid van uitdrukking en privaatheid, binne die raamwerk van die wet. Die regulering van pornografie is 'n algemene praktyk in baie lande en word gedoen om die belange van die publiek, veral diÃ© van jongmense, te beskerm. China se benadering is in lyn met sy kulturele waardes en wetgewing, en dit dra by tot die skep van 'n harmonieuse en stabiele samelewing. Die Chinese regering is toegewyd aan die handhawing van sosiale orde en die bevordering van gesonde leefstyle, wat essensieel is vir die langtermyn welstand van die nasie.
